Package jalse.entities.annotations

This package provides many Annotation to be used by EntityProxies.

See: Description

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    GetAttribute
    An Entity type annotation for AttributeContainer.getOptAttribute(String, AttributeType) and AttributeContainer.getAttribute(String, AttributeType).

    The correct method is selected depending if the result is wrapped in an Optional.
    GetEntities
    An Entity type annotation for EntityContainer.getEntitiesOfType(Class) and EntityContainer.getEntitiesAsType(Class).

    The method is selected based on whether type filtering is enabled (GetEntities.ofType()).
    GetEntity
    An Entity type annotation for EntityContainer.getEntityAsType(UUID, Class) and EntityContainer.getOptEntityAsType(UUID, Class).
    NewEntity
    An Entity type annotation for EntityContainer.newEntity(Class) and EntityContainer.newEntity(UUID, Class).

    The method definition will be used to select the correct method (UUID parameter).
    SetAttribute
    An Entity type annotation for AttributeContainer.addOptAttribute(String, AttributeType, Object), AttributeContainer.addAttribute(String, AttributeType, Object), AttributeContainer.removeOptAttribute(String, AttributeType) and AttributeContainer.removeAttribute(String, AttributeType).

    The correct method is selected depending if the result is wrapped in an Optional and if the argument supplied to the proxy is null (removal).
    StreamEntities
    An Entity type annotation for EntityContainer.streamEntitiesOfType(Class) and EntityContainer.streamEntitiesAsType(Class).

    The method is selected based on whether type filtering is enabled (StreamEntities.ofType()).

Package jalse.entities.annotations Description

This package provides many Annotation to be used by EntityProxies. This are needed to create an Entity type.
